.SH NAME
jref \- JSON Reference CLI tool for condensed JSON project snapshots
.
.SH SYNOPSIS
.SY jref
[\fB\-\-json\fR|\fB\-j\fR]
[\fB\-\-silent\fR|\fB\-s\fR]
[\fB\-\-raw\fR|\fB\-r\fR]
[\fB\-\-jq\fR|\fB\-q\fR \fIfilter\fR]
[\fB\-\-help\fR|\fB\-h\fR]
[\fB\-\-version\fR|\fB\-v\fR]
.IR command
[\fIarguments\fR...]
.YS
.PP
The following commands are available:
.IR alias ,
.IR bextract ,
.IR bin ,
.IR bpack ,
.IR config ,
.IR diff ,
.IR extract ,
.IR flatten ,
.IR get ,
.IR graph ,
.IR inspect ,
.IR mount ,
.IR openapi ,
.IR pack ,
.IR patch ,
.IR query ,
.IR reconstruct ,
.IR run ,
.IR search ,
.IR serve ,
.IR set ,
.IR shell ,
.IR summarize ,
.IR tool ,
.IR ui ,
.IR unflatten ,
.IR validate .
.
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B jref
(JSON Reference) is a CLI tool for creating, inspecting, searching,
and manipulating condensed JSON project snapshots.
A snapshot is a single JSON file containing a directory tree,
all file contents keyed by path, and optional AI instructions or
project metadata.
.PP
Snapshots are designed to be portable, streamable for large files,
and AI-friendly with structured JSON I/O and an MCP server mode.
An interactive Terminal UI is also available for visual browsing.
.PP
All commands accept stdin pipe input, e.g.:
.B "cat snapshot.json | jref inspect" .
.
.SH GLOBAL OPTIONS
These flags apply to any command and must appear before the command
name.
.TP 4
.B \-\-json\fR, \fB\-j
Output structured JSON instead of human-readable text.
Every command supports this.
.TP
.B \-\-silent\fR, \fB\-s
Suppress all decorative output, progress indicators, and ASCII art.
.TP
.B \-\-raw\fR, \fB\-r
Raw output mode.
For the
.B query
command this emits pure file content without headers or labels.
.TP
.B \-\-jq\fR, \fB\-q \fIfilter
Apply a
.B jq
filter to reshape or filter the snapshot state in memory before any core command receives it.
Uses \fBjq-wasm\fR for portability across ARM and x86 devices.
.TP
.B \-\-help\fR, \fB\-h
Show global help listing all commands.
Append to any specific command for command-specific help:
.B "jref pack \-\-help" .
.TP
.B \-\-version\fR, \fB\-v
Print the version string
.B "jref v1.2.0" .
Use with
.B \-\-json
to get
.BR "{\e"version\e": \e"1.2.0\e"}" .
.
.SH COMMANDS
.
.SS ALIAS
Create and manage command shortcuts for complex or frequent workflows.
.PP
.B "jref alias <action> [name] [expansion]"
.PP
.B ACTIONS
.RS 4
.TP 4
.B set \fIname\fR \fIexp\fR
Create or update an alias.
.TP
.B remove \fIname\fR
Delete an alias.
.TP
.B list
List all active aliases.
.RE
.PP
.B EXAMPLES
.PP
.EX
jref alias set map "summarize --compress"
jref map project.json
.EE
.
.SS BEXTRACT
Unpack a JSON binary archive back to the filesystem. Specialized for large assets.
.PP
.B "jref bextract \fIfile\fR [\fIoptions\fR] [\fIpatterns...\fR]"
.PP
.B OPTIONS
.RS 4
.TP 4
.B \-\-output, \-o \fIdir\fR
Target directory (default: ./extracted).
.TP
.B \-\-overwrite, \-w
Overwrite existing files.
.TP
.B \-\-dry\-run
Show what would be extracted.
.TP
.B \-\-stdout
Pipes a single decoded asset directly to stdout.
.RE
.
.SS BIN
Manage virtual binaries and executable scripts stored within snapshots.
.PP
.B "jref bin \fIaction\fR [\fIargs...\fR]"
.PP
.B ACTIONS
.RS 4
.TP 4
.B list
List all virtual binaries in $JREF_BIN_PATH.
.TP
.B exec \fIname\fR [\fIargs\fR]
Execute a virtual binary.
.TP
.B setup
Interactive setup of the bin environment.
.RE
.PP
\fBNote:\fR When linked, the \fBjbin\fR command automatically executes the \fBbin\fR command.
.
.SS BPACK
Specialized binary-first snapshot creation for large datasets and assets.
.PP
.B "jref bpack [\fIdirectory\fR] [\fIoptions\fR]"
.PP
.B OPTIONS
.RS 4
.TP 4
.B \-\-output, \-o \fIfile\fR
Output filename (default: stdout).
.TP
.B \-\-exclude \fIpattern\fR
Exclude files matching pattern.
.TP
.B \-\-max\-size \fIbytes\fR
Limit maximum size of a single binary file.
.RE
.
.SS CONFIG
Persistent CLI configuration management.
.PP
.B "jref config \fIaction\fR [\fIkey\fR] [\fIvalue\fR]"
.PP
.B ACTIONS
.RS 4
.TP 4
.B set \fIkey\fR \fIval\fR
Update a configuration setting.
.TP
.B get \fIkey\fR
View a configuration setting.
.TP
.B list
Show all current settings.
.TP
.B ui
Open the interactive configuration TUI.
.RE
.PP
.B SETTINGS
.RS 4
.IP \(bu 2
\fBdefaultOutput\fR: json, pretty, raw
.IP \(bu 2
\fBtheme\fR: dark, light, system
.IP \(bu 2
\fBsilent\fR: true, false
.IP \(bu 2
\fBaliasToggle\fR: true, false
.RE
.
.SS DIFF
Compare snapshot contents against the local filesystem.
.PP
.B "jref diff [\fIoptions\fR] [\fIfile.json\fR]"
.PP
.B OPTIONS
.RS 4
.TP 4
.B \-\-directory, \-d \fIdir\fR
Target directory to compare against (default: current directory).
.TP
.B \-\-all, \-a
Find extra local files not in snapshot.
.RE
.PP
.B EXAMPLES
.PP
.EX
jref diff snapshot.json
jref diff --directory ./my-app snapshot.json
.EE
.
.SS EXTRACT
Unpack files from a snapshot back into the local filesystem. Supports wildcards and directory prefixes.
.PP
.B "jref extract [\fIoptions\fR] [\fIfile\fR] [\fIpatterns...\fR]"
.PP
.B OPTIONS
.RS 4
.TP 4
.B \-\-output \fIdir\fR, \fB\-o \fIdir\fR
Destination directory. Defaults to \fB./extracted\fR.
.TP
.B \-\-overwrite, \-w
Overwrite existing files on disk.
.TP
.B \-\-dry\-run, \-n
Preview what would be extracted without writing any files.
.TP
.B \-\-flat
Extract files into a single directory (no subfolders).
.TP
.B \-\-stdout
Pipe a single decoded asset directly to stdout.
.TP
.B \-\-listen
Listen on stdin for continuous stream of snapshots/deltas (RPC mode).
.RE
.PP
.B EXAMPLES
.PP
.EX
jref extract snapshot.json
jref extract snapshot.json "src/**/*.ts"
jref extract --stdout snapshot.json "kick.wav" | ./dsp_tool
jref extract --listen --output ./mirror
.EE
.
.SS FLATTEN
Flatten a nested snapshot into a one-level key-value map.
.PP
.B "jref flatten [\fIfile.json\fR]"
.PP
Useful for legacy tool compatibility or simplified parsing.
.
.SS GET
Retrieve specific data nodes from a snapshot using dot-notation.
.PP
.B "jref get \fIpath\fR [\fIfile.json\fR]"
.PP
.B EXAMPLES
.PP
.EX
jref get instruction project.json
jref get "files.src/index.ts" project.json
.EE
.
.SS GRAPH
Analyze and visualize dependency relationships between symbols and modules.
.PP
.B "jref graph \fIsubcommand\fR [\fItarget\fR] [\fIoptions\fR]"
.PP
.B SUBCOMMANDS
.RS 4
.TP 4
.B build \fItarget\fR
Build the knowledge graph from directory or snapshot.
.TP
.B query \fItarget\fR \fIargs\fR
Query the knowledge graph (experimental).
.TP
.B wasm\-update
Pre-fetch registered WASM binaries for offline use.
.TP
.B ui \fItarget\fR
Start a local web server to visualize the graph.
.RE
.PP
.B OPTIONS
.RS 4
.TP 4
.B \-\-output, \-o \fIfile\fR
Save graph data to a file.
.TP
.B \-\-format \fIfmt\fR
Output format: \fBjson\fR, \fBdot\fR, \fBmermaid\fR (default: \fBjson\fR).
.TP
.B \-\-depth \fIn\fR
Traversal depth (default: 1).
.TP
.B \-\-cluster
Detect and highlight modular clusters (Louvain method).
.TP
.B \-\-centrality
Highlight high-impact nodes using degree centrality.
.TP
.B \-\-no\-llm
Skip semantic extraction using LLM.
.TP
.B \-p, \-\-port \fIn\fR
Port for the graph UI server (default: 8080).
.RE
.PP
.B EXAMPLES
.PP
.EX
jref graph build .
jref graph ui
.EE
.
.SS INSPECT
View snapshot metadata and directory tree without loading the entire
file into memory.
.PP
.B "jref inspect [\fIoptions\fR] [\fIfile\fR]"
.PP
.B OPTIONS
.RS 4
.TP 4
.B \-\-metadata, \-m
Show only snapshot metadata.
.TP 4
.B \-\-structure, \-t
Show only the ASCII directory tree.
.TP
.B \-\-files, \-f
Show only the list of file paths.
.TP
.B \-\-summary
Show instruction/summary/header fields.
.RE
.
.SS MOUNT
Mount a snapshot as a virtual filesystem and expose it via WebDAV.
.PP
.B "jref mount \fIfile.json\fR [\fIoptions\fR]"
.PP
.B OPTIONS
.RS 4
.TP 4
.B \-\-port, \-p \fIn\fR
Port for the WebDAV server (default: 8080).
.TP
.B \-\-read\-only
Mount in read-only mode.
.RE
.
.SS OPENAPI
Transform an OpenAPI/RESTful specification into a queryable jref snapshot.
.PP
.B "jref openapi \fIspec.json\fR"
.PP
.B EXAMPLES
.PP
.EX
jref openapi api.json > snapshot.json
jref openapi api.json | jref ui
.EE
.
.SS PACK
Create a jref snapshot from a local directory or remote repository (optimized for LLMs).
.PP
.B "jref pack [directory|url] [options]"
.PP
.B OPTIONS
.RS 4
.TP 4
.B \-\-semantic
Enable AST-aware semantic chunking and local embeddings.
.TP
.B \-\-instruction \fItext\fR
Add custom AI instructions (auto-generated if omitted).
.TP
.B \-\-summary \fItext\fR
Add a high-level file summary.
.TP
.B \-\-max\-size \fIbytes\fR
Split snapshot into chunks (JSON only).
.TP
.B \-s, \-\-output\-style \fIstyle\fR
Output format: \fBjson\fR, \fBmarkdown\fR, \fBxml\fR, \fBplain\fR.
.TP
.B \-\-branch \fIname\fR
Target specific branch (remote).
.TP
.B \-\-commit \fIhash\fR
Target specific commit (remote).
.TP
.B \-\-compress
Enable AST-aware whitespace removal.
.TP
.B \-\-remove\-comments
Strip code comments.
.TP
.B \-\-remove\-empty\-lines
Strip blank lines.
.TP
.B \-\-token\-limit \fIn\fR
Cap the total output tokens.
.TP
.B \-\-hashes
Output a hash map of the directory instead of a snapshot.
.TP
.B \-\-delta [\fIremote-hashes\fR]
Create a delta snapshot based on remote hashes.
.TP
.B \-\-stream
Enable real-time streaming mode for piped synchronization.
.RE
.PP
.B EXAMPLES
.PP
.EX
jref pack . --compress > project.json
jref pack https://github.com/user/repo --branch main > remote.json
.EE
.
.SS PATCH
Update or add files and metadata in a snapshot without extraction.
.PP
.B "jref patch [path] [content] [file.json] [options]"
.PP
.B OPTIONS
.RS 4
.TP 4
.B \-\-instruction \fItext\fR
Update snapshot instructions.
.TP
.B \-\-summary \fItext\fR
Update snapshot summary.
.RE
.PP
.B EXAMPLES
.PP
.EX
jref patch src/main.ts "new code" project.json > updated.json
cat fix.ts | jref patch src/main.ts project.json > updated.json
.EE
.
.SS QUERY
Get content of a specific file path or perform natural language Semantic Search (RAG).
.PP
.B "jref query [options] [file]"
.PP
.B OPTIONS
.RS 4
.TP 4
.B \-\-path, \-p \fIpath\fR
Path of the file to query.
.TP
.B \-\-semantic, \-s \fIquery\fR
Perform natural language search across code chunks.
.TP
.B \-\-top\-k \fIn\fR
Number of results for semantic search (default: 5).
.TP
.B \-\-raw, \-r
Emit pure content without headers.
.RE
.PP
.B EXAMPLES
.PP
.EX
jref query --path "src/main.ts" snapshot.json
jref query --semantic "How are tokens handled?" snapshot.json
.EE
.
.SS RECONSTRUCT
Verify if a local directory matches the snapshot (dry-run mode).
.PP
.B "jref reconstruct [\fIoptions\fR] [\fIfile\fR]"
.PP
.B OPTIONS
.RS 4
.TP 4
.B \-\-directory, \-d \fIdir\fR
Target directory to verify (default: current directory).
.TP
.B \-\-verbose, \-v
Show detailed comparison results.
.TP
.B \-\-ignore\-missing
Do not fail if files from the snapshot are missing locally.
.TP
.B \-\-ignore\-extra
Do not fail if extra local files are found.
.RE
.
.SS RUN
Execute a script directly from the JSON snapshot without permanent extraction.
.PP
.B "jref run \fB\-\-path\fR \fIpath\fR [\fIfile\fR] [\fIscript-args...\fR]"
.PP
.B OPTIONS
.RS 4
.TP 4
.B \-\-path, \-p \fIpath\fR
Path to the script within the snapshot.
.RE
.
.SS SEARCH
High-speed regex or keyword searching across all entries.
.PP
.B "jref search \fIpattern\fR [\fIoptions\fR] [\fIfile\fR]"
.
.SS SERVE
Start a Model Context Protocol (MCP) server for agentic interoperability.
.PP
.B "jref serve [\fIfile.json\fR]"
.PP
.B MCP TOOLS EXPOSED
.RS 4
.TP 4
.B inspect
Get metadata and structure.
.TP
.B search
Regex search across files.
.TP
.B query
Read specific file content.
.TP
.B jq_query
Execute jq filter against snapshot.
.TP
.B summarize
Get token-efficient map of specific files.
.TP
.B list_directory
Localized tree inspection (ls style).
.TP
.B find_references
Cross-file symbol reference tracing.
.RE
.
.SS SET
Update or create specific nodes in a snapshot using dot-notation.
.PP
.B "jref set \fIpath\fR \fIvalue\fR [\fIfile.json\fR]"
.PP
.B EXAMPLES
.PP
.EX
jref set instruction "New AI prompt" project.json
jref set "files.README.md" "New content" project.json
.EE
.
.SS SHELL
Launch an interactive JavaScript REPL to manipulate snapshots in real-time.
.PP
.B "jref shell [\fIfile.json\fR]"
.PP
Available in shell: \fBctx\fR (snapshot), \fBfiles\fR (alias), \fB.save\fR, \fB.reload\fR.
.
.SS SUMMARIZE
Generate a token-efficient architectural map by stripping implementation details.
.PP
.B "jref summarize [\fIfile.json\fR]"
.
.SS TOOL
Execute external commands and parse their output directly into snapshots.
.PP
.B "jref tool \fIname\fR \fIcommand\fR [\fIargs...\fR]"
.PP
.B PARSERS AVAILABLE
.RS 4
.IP \(bu 2
\fBls\fR: Standard directory listing to JSON.
.IP \(bu 2
\fBgit\-log\fR: Git history to structured JSON.
.IP \(bu 2
\fBps\fR: Process list to structured JSON.
.RE
.PP
.B EXAMPLES
.PP
.EX
jref tool ls "ls -la" > files.json
.EE
.
.SS UI
Interactive Terminal User Interface for browsing snapshots.
.PP
.B "jref ui [\fIfile\fR]"
.
.SS UNFLATTEN
Restore a flattened snapshot back to its original nested structure.
.PP
.B "jref unflatten [\fIfile.json\fR]"
.
.SS VALIDATE
Analyze git diff blast radius and generate AI validation context.
.PP
.B "jref validate \fItarget-branch\fR [\fIoptions\fR]"
.PP
.B OPTIONS
.RS 4
.TP 4
.B \-\-output, \-o \fIfile\fR
Output the validation snapshot to a file.
.TP
.B \-\-depth, \-d \fIn\fR
Maximum depth for dependency traversal (default: 1).
.TP
.B \-\-all, \-a
Include all tracked files (ignores blast radius).
.RE
.
.SH SNAPSHOT SCHEMA
A valid jref snapshot is a JSON object with this structure:
.PP
.EX
{
  "directoryStructure": "ASCII tree string (required)",
  "files": {
    "path/to/file1.ts": "file content string (required)",
    "path/to/file2.py": "file content string"
  },
  "instruction": "AI system prompt context (optional)",
  "fileSummary": "Human-readable project overview (optional)",
  "userProvidedHeader": "Custom header note (optional)"
}
.EE
.
.SH TARGET ENVIRONMENTS
.B jref
is engineered for constrained computing environments:
.TP 4
Termux (Android/ARM)
Full clipboard integration via \fBtermux-clipboard-set\fR.
.TP
Raspberry Pi 4 (ARM)
Chunked streaming for large snapshots; minimal memory footprint.
.TP
Standard Linux (x86)
Full feature set.
.TP
macOS
Full feature set; \fBpbcopy\fR for clipboard integration.
.
.SH EXIT CODES
.TP 4
.B 0
Success.
.TP
.B 1
General error: file not found, invalid arguments, parse error.
.TP
.B 2
Query target file not found in snapshot.
.
